<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wall Art: Drawings and pastels from the 1982 film "Pink Floyd the Wall" will go 
on display at Christie's Los Angeles in Beverly Hills on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Artwork from the film's animated sequences, designed by Gerald Scarfe, will be 
sold at Christie's South Kensington on Sept. 21. Pre-sale estimates range from 
$270 to $2,700. This auction will also include a selection of signed items and 
props from the "The Wall" performance that Pink Floyd gave this summer at the 
Berlin Wall, which will be sold to benefit the Memorial Fund for Disaster 
Relief.BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
